WEBVTT

00:01.370 --> 00:02.826
[narrator]
Previously, on Queen Sugar.

00:02.870 --> 00:05.668
[Darla]
I cant take Blue away from
the only family hes ever known.

00:05.710 --> 00:08.998
-Were his family too.
-Im asking

00:09.050 --> 00:11.666
-for 70/30 split for custody.
-Youre out your mind.

00:11.720 --> 00:13.927
The New Yorker,
they want to publish

00:13.970 --> 00:15.710
the chapter on your dads
depression.

00:15.760 --> 00:18.502
Sam has run this familys legacy
into the ground.

00:18.560 --> 00:19.800
I need him out.

00:19.850 --> 00:21.226
You can help me do that.

00:21.270 --> 00:22.476
Please dont hate me.

00:22.520 --> 00:25.978
Remy and I, we kissed.

00:26.020 --> 00:28.068
[Malik]
Oh, no, no, we need to put
that out right now.

00:28.110 --> 00:29.816
-[gunshot]
-Go, go, go!

00:32.990 --> 00:35.697
[Nova]
My mama was my north star.

00:35.740 --> 00:38.868
Free. Fierce.

00:38.910 --> 00:41.367
A warrior.

00:41.410 --> 00:43.901
My mama was...

00:43.960 --> 00:46.281
the ground
beneath my feet.

00:48.000 --> 00:49.456
But the day
the sickness came,

00:49.500 --> 00:54.005
the trees shook
and the ground swayed.

00:54.050 --> 00:58.464
And at 19, I let out a cry
in this earthquake of sorrow.

01:02.930 --> 01:04.261
She was my everything.

01:11.900 --> 01:16.906
Grief and confusion wedged into
every corner of my universe.

01:16.950 --> 01:20.738
Where her bright light
once charted my way,

01:20.790 --> 01:23.577
everything went dark.

01:26.710 --> 01:28.496
But an hour from New Orleans

01:28.540 --> 01:30.531
on the other side
of Lake Pontchartrain,

01:30.590 --> 01:33.206
deep in the stalks
of the cane fields,

01:33.260 --> 01:38.505
my sweet daddys tears
quenched the earth.

01:38.550 --> 01:42.008
I never knew that
that the land,

01:42.060 --> 01:44.676
and my mamas grave
beneath it,

01:44.730 --> 01:46.800
were more than
he could bear.

01:49.360 --> 01:51.316
My daddy was the land.

01:53.650 --> 01:57.484
And we were generations
of earth.

01:59.320 --> 02:01.117
From the nooses
withered in the trees

02:01.160 --> 02:02.980
to the blood-drenched
ground.

02:05.500 --> 02:07.070
Daddy would spend a lifetime

02:07.120 --> 02:09.327
fertilizing the earth
to grow anew.

02:11.500 --> 02:13.582
He fought hard.

02:15.050 --> 02:17.462
Every farming grant denied.

02:17.510 --> 02:20.388
Every deed contested.

02:20.430 --> 02:22.671
Every plantation owner
come a-knockin,

02:22.720 --> 02:24.210
trying to take
what was ours.

02:26.390 --> 02:28.438
He always stood tall

02:28.480 --> 02:31.938
and strong in those
mud-caked boots.

02:34.480 --> 02:36.607
But the day
her sickness came,

02:36.650 --> 02:39.141
he slowly started
bleeding out.

02:41.070 --> 02:45.109
The stars, her star
that once lit his sky,

02:45.160 --> 02:46.866
went dark.

02:48.580 --> 02:51.287
So he walked the furrows
with a gun

02:51.330 --> 02:53.787
in the worn corduroy jacket

02:53.840 --> 02:56.297
he used to warmed me with
on chilly nights.

02:57.630 --> 02:59.370
He walked for hours

02:59.430 --> 03:01.637
in a forest of cane,

03:01.680 --> 03:05.218
and buried in a casket
of sorrow.

03:07.810 --> 03:11.189
Unable to see her star.

03:14.730 --> 03:17.278
Holding that gun,
fingers curled...

03:19.030 --> 03:21.316
among generations
that walked before,

03:21.360 --> 03:24.443
grieving, bleeding...

03:26.830 --> 03:29.572
I never knew the depth
of his pain.

03:32.710 --> 03:36.373
But as the whispers of our
ancestors lifted from the ground

03:36.420 --> 03:38.206
and carried him
in the breeze,

03:38.260 --> 03:42.924
his fingers uncurled
and he loosened his grip,

03:42.970 --> 03:47.384
guiding him to the break
in the field.

03:47.430 --> 03:51.389
And at the edge of the land
he found us.

03:53.270 --> 03:54.851
Waiting.

03:56.440 --> 03:59.227
Arms opened.

04:04.530 --> 04:05.815
Thank you.

04:05.870 --> 04:07.826
[applause]

04:21.010 --> 04:22.750
Dreams never die

